<subpara id="RM000000PFW01NX_02" type-id="64" category="03" proc-id="RM0250U___00002RI00000">
<name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name>
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>The ECM monitors the battery supply voltage applied to the throttle actuator.</ptxt>
<ptxt>When the power supply voltage (+BM) drops below 4 V for 0.8 seconds or more, the ECM interprets this as an open in the power supply circuit (+BM). The ECM illuminates the MIL and sets the DTC.</ptxt>
<ptxt>If the malfunction is not repaired successfully, the DTC is set 5 seconds after the engine is next started.</ptxt>
</content5>
</subpara>
